 {"id":"bd-10i.3.3","title":"Implement CellAttrs with StyleFlags","description":"# Implement CellAttrs with StyleFlags

## Objective
Implement the 4-byte packed attributes type that holds style flags and link ID.

## Technical Design

### Layout
[31-24: flags (8 bits)][23-0: link_id (24 bits)]

### StyleFlags (8 bits)
Using bitflags crate for ergonomic flag manipulation:
- BOLD (1 << 0)
- DIM (1 << 1)
- ITALIC (1 << 2)
- UNDERLINE (1 << 3)
- BLINK (1 << 4)
- REVERSE (1 << 5)
- STRIKETHROUGH (1 << 6)
- HIDDEN (1 << 7)

### Link ID (24 bits)
- 0 = no link
- 1-16777214 = valid link IDs from LinkRegistry
- Allows ~16 million unique links per frame

### Implementation
bitflags::bitflags! {
    #[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Debug)]
    pub struct StyleFlags: u8 {
        const BOLD          = 0b0000_0001;
        const DIM           = 0b0000_0010;
        const ITALIC        = 0b0000_0100;
        const UNDERLINE     = 0b0000_1000;
        const BLINK         = 0b0001_0000;
        const REVERSE       = 0b0010_0000;
        const STRIKETHROUGH = 0b0100_0000;
        const HIDDEN        = 0b1000_0000;
    }
}

#[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Default)]
#[repr(transparent)]
pub struct CellAttrs(u32);

impl CellAttrs {
    pub const NONE: Self = Self(0);

    #[inline]
    pub fn new(flags: StyleFlags, link_id: u32) -> Self {
        debug_assert!(link_id < 0x00FF_FFFF, 'link_id overflow');
        Self(((flags.bits() as u32) << 24) | (link_id & 0x00FF_FFFF))
    }

    #[inline]
    pub fn flags(&self) -> StyleFlags {
        StyleFlags::from_bits_truncate((self.0 >> 24) as u8)
    }

    #[inline]
    pub fn link_id(&self) -> u32 {
        self.0 & 0x00FF_FFFF
    }

    #[inline]
    pub fn with_flags(self, flags: StyleFlags) -> Self {
        Self((self.0 & 0x00FF_FFFF) | ((flags.bits() as u32) << 24))
    }

    #[inline]
    pub fn with_link(self, link_id: u32) -> Self {
        Self((self.0 & 0xFF00_0000) | (link_id & 0x00FF_FFFF))
    }

    #[inline]
    pub fn has_flag(&self, flag: StyleFlags) -> bool {
        self.flags().contains(flag)
    }
}

