 {"id":"bd-10i.3.4","title":"Implement Cell struct (16 bytes)","description":"# Implement Cell struct (16 bytes)

## Objective
Implement the complete Cell struct that combines all components into exactly 16 bytes.

## Technical Design

### Layout
#[repr(C, align(16))]
pub struct Cell {
    pub content: CellContent,  // 4 bytes (offset 0)
    pub fg: PackedRgba,        // 4 bytes (offset 4)
    pub bg: PackedRgba,        // 4 bytes (offset 8)
    pub attrs: CellAttrs,      // 4 bytes (offset 12)
}
// Total: 16 bytes, aligned to 16-byte boundary

### Why repr(C, align(16))?
- Predictable memory layout
- 4 cells per 64-byte cache line
- Enables SIMD comparison (128-bit)
- No padding surprises

### Special Cells
- CONTINUATION: Placeholder for second column of wide chars
  - content = 0xFFFF_FFFF (invalid Unicode)
  - Used when wide char occupies 2 cells

### Implementation
impl Default for Cell {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            content: CellContent::EMPTY,
            fg: PackedRgba::WHITE,
            bg: PackedRgba::TRANSPARENT,
            attrs: CellAttrs::NONE,
        }
    }
}

impl Cell {
    pub const CONTINUATION: Self = Self {
        content: CellContent(0xFFFF_FFFF),
        fg: PackedRgba::TRANSPARENT,
        bg: PackedRgba::TRANSPARENT,
        attrs: CellAttrs::NONE,
    };

    #[inline]
    pub fn is_continuation(&self) -> bool {
        self.content.0 == 0xFFFF_FFFF
    }

    /// Bitwise equality (fast path for diffing)
    #[inline]
    pub fn bits_eq(&self, other: &Self) -> bool {
        self.content == other.content &&
        self.fg == other.fg &&
        self.bg == other.bg &&
        self.attrs == other.attrs
    }

    #[inline]
    pub fn width(&self) -> usize {
        self.content.width()
    }

    // Builder methods
    pub fn char(c: char) -> Self {
        Self {
            content: CellContent::from_char(c),
            ..Default::default()
        }
    }

    pub fn fg(mut self, color: PackedRgba) -> Self {
        self.fg = color;
        self
    }

    pub fn bg(mut self, color: PackedRgba) -> Self {
        self.bg = color;
        self
    }

    pub fn attrs(mut self, attrs: CellAttrs) -> Self {
        self.attrs = attrs;
        self
    }
}

impl PartialEq for Cell {
    fn eq(&self, other: &Self) -> bool {
        self.bits_eq(other)
    }
}

impl Eq for Cell {}

