## Objective
Implement the reference-counted pool for complex grapheme clusters (emoji, ZWJ sequences).

## Why GraphemePool?
Most cells are simple ASCII or BMP characters that fit in CellContent's 4 bytes directly. But some graphemes (emoji with skin tone, ZWJ sequences like family emoji) require multiple Unicode codepoints and variable-length strings.

The pool:
- Stores these complex strings once
- Returns a compact GraphemeId (4 bytes)
- Reference counts for memory management
- Reuses slots from free list

## Technical Design

### Slot Structure
struct GraphemeSlot {
    text: String,      // The actual grapheme string
    width: u8,         // Display width (0-127)
    refcount: u32,     // Reference count
}

### Pool Structure
pub struct GraphemePool {
    strings: Vec<Option<GraphemeSlot>>,  // Slot storage
    lookup: HashMap<String, GraphemeId>, // Fast dedup
    free_list: Vec<u32>,                 // Reusable slots
}

### Implementation
impl GraphemePool {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Self {
            strings: Vec::new(),
            lookup: HashMap::new(),
            free_list: Vec::new(),
        }
    }

    /// Intern a grapheme, returning existing ID if present
    pub fn intern(&mut self, s: &str) -> GraphemeId {
        // Check if already interned
        if let Some(&id) = self.lookup.get(s) {
            self.incref(id);
            return id;
        }

        // Calculate display width
        let width = unicode_width::UnicodeWidthStr::width(s)
            .min(127) as u8;

        // Find or create slot
        let slot_idx = self.free_list.pop().unwrap_or_else(|| {
            let idx = self.strings.len() as u32;
            self.strings.push(None);
            idx
        });

        let id = GraphemeId::new(slot_idx, width);
        self.strings[slot_idx as usize] = Some(GraphemeSlot {
            text: s.to_string(),
            width,
            refcount: 1,
        });
        self.lookup.insert(s.to_string(), id);
        id
    }

    /// Get string for ID
    pub fn get(&self, id: GraphemeId) -> Option<&str> {
        self.strings.get(id.slot())
            .and_then(|slot| slot.as_ref())
            .map(|s| s.text.as_str())
    }

    /// Increment refcount
    fn incref(&mut self, id: GraphemeId) {
        if let Some(Some(slot)) = self.strings.get_mut(id.slot()) {
            slot.refcount = slot.refcount.saturating_add(1);
        }
    }

    /// Decrement refcount, freeing if zero
    pub fn decref(&mut self, id: GraphemeId) {
        let slot_idx = id.slot();
        if let Some(Some(slot)) = self.strings.get_mut(slot_idx) {
            slot.refcount = slot.refcount.saturating_sub(1);
            if slot.refcount == 0 {
                self.lookup.remove(&slot.text);
                self.strings[slot_idx] = None;
                self.free_list.push(slot_idx as u32);
            }
        }
    }

    pub fn len(&self) -> usize {
        self.strings.iter().filter(|s| s.is_some()).count()
    }
}

## Invariants
- slot.refcount > 0 implies slot is valid
- GraphemeId only created via pool.intern()
- lookup and strings are consistent
- Free list contains only None slots

## Tests Required
- [ ] intern() returns same ID for same string
- [ ] intern() increments refcount on reuse
- [ ] get() retrieves correct string
- [ ] decref() frees at refcount 0
- [ ] Free list reuses slots
- [ ] Width calculation correct for emoji
- [ ] ZWJ sequences handled

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All invariants maintained
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Intern hit: < 100ns
