 {"id":"bd-10i.3.6","title":"Implement Buffer with scissor/opacity stacks","description":"# Implement Buffer with scissor/opacity stacks

## Background & Strategic Importance
The Buffer is the central data structure of the rendering pipeline - the 2D grid of Cells that widgets render into and the Presenter reads from. It has the highest bottleneck score (367.5) in the dependency graph because 13+ downstream tasks depend on it.

**Why This Is Critical:**
- Every widget renders to a Buffer
- BufferDiff compares Buffers
- Presenter reads Buffers
- Frame wraps a Buffer
- All layout calculations target Buffer dimensions

---

## Technical Design

### Core Structure

```rust
use tracing::{debug, trace, instrument};

/// 2D grid of cells with scissor (clipping) and opacity stacks.
///
/// # Design Rationale
/// - Row-major layout for cache efficiency during diffing
/// - Scissor stack for nested clipping (widget boundaries)
/// - Opacity stack for transparency compositing
/// - Both stacks always have at least one element (invariant)
pub struct Buffer {
    width: u16,
    height: u16,
    cells: Vec<Cell>,
    /// Stack of clipping rectangles; writes outside current scissor are ignored
    scissor_stack: Vec<Rect>,
    /// Stack of opacity multipliers; applied to cell colors on write
    opacity_stack: Vec<f32>,
}
```

### Invariants (MUST be tested)

1. `cells.len() == width * height` (always, after construction)
2. `width` and `height` are immutable after creation
3. Scissor intersection monotonically decreases on push (can only shrink)
4. Opacity product stays in [0.0, 1.0] range
5. Both stacks always have at least one element (can't pop below base)
6. Wide character at x sets x+1 to CONTINUATION

### Constructor

```rust
impl Buffer {
    /// Create new buffer filled with default (empty) cells.
    ///
    /// # Panics
    /// Panics if width*height would overflow usize.
    pub fn new(width: u16, height: u16) -> Self {
        let size = (width as usize)
            .checked_mul(height as usize)
            .expect("Buffer size overflow");
        debug!(width, height, size, "Creating Buffer");

        Self {
            width,
            height,
            cells: vec![Cell::default(); size],
            scissor_stack: vec![Rect::new(0, 0, width, height)],
            opacity_stack: vec![1.0],
        }
    }

    /// Create from existing area (convenience for widget rendering).
    pub fn empty(area: Rect) -> Self {
        Self::new(area.width, area.height)
    }
}
```

### Cell Access

```rust
impl Buffer {
    // --- Dimensions ---

    #[inline]
    pub fn width(&self) -> u16 { self.width }

    #[inline]
    pub fn height(&self) -> u16 { self.height }

    #[inline]
    pub fn area(&self) -> Rect {
        Rect::new(0, 0, self.width, self.height)
    }

    // --- Index calculation ---

    #[inline]
    fn index(&self, x: u16, y: u16) -> usize {
        (y as usize) * (self.width as usize) + (x as usize)
    }

    // --- Safe access ---

    /// Get cell at (x, y) with bounds check.
    #[inline]
    pub fn get(&self, x: u16, y: u16) -> Option<&Cell> {
        if x < self.width && y < self.height {
            Some(&self.cells[self.index(x, y)])
        } else {
            None
        }
    }

    /// Get mutable cell at (x, y) with bounds check.
    #[inline]
    pub fn get_mut(&mut self, x: u16, y: u16) -> Option<&mut Cell> {
        if x < self.width && y < self.height {
            let idx = self.index(x, y);
            Some(&mut self.cells[idx])
        } else {
            None
        }
    }

    // --- Unchecked access (for hot paths like diffing) ---

    /// Get cell without bounds check. Caller must ensure x < width && y < height.
    #[inline]
    pub fn get_unchecked(&self, x: u16, y: u16) -> &Cell {
        debug_assert!(x < self.width && y < self.height);
        &self.cells[self.index(x, y)]
    }

    /// Raw cell slice for iteration.
    pub fn cells(&self) -> &[Cell] {
        &self.cells
    }
